        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        ooh, someone’s late as usual. i’ll just do a traffic light review.

        🔴 (negative)
        1) commitment issues, patience, and all you ever wanted continue to fall.
        2) sadly, i don’t get the appeal for body. i like drill music but this just isn’t it.
        3) didn’t know didn’t really impress me either. still, it’s not as bad as the disaster that was you want me, from 2016.
        4) just found out that streets and latest trends are going on acr next week... noooo!

        🟠 (mixed)
        1) i don’t mind montero staying at number 1 for another week, but it better not stay there forever, or else i’ll be tired of it.
        2) peaches has climbed to the runner-up spot! this might end up in the green section someday, with how much it’s growing on me.
        3) on one hand, i’m glad that let’s go home together didnt move at all, but on the other hand, i’m still disappointed it’s this high up.
        4) i’m indifferent on the slight fall for good without! it’s cooling off on me a lot, but i still think it’s okay.
        5) head & heart and what’s next fell out the top 40.
        6) the snuts got the number 1 album this week - only here because i haven’t heard it yet.

        🟢 (positive)
        1) heat waves is moving closer to the top 20! i love this song so much, i hope it gets there.
        2) i’m also loving the gains for heartbreak anniversary, rasputin, black hole, and ferrari horses.
        3) deja vu is the highest new entry of the week! it’s not in the same tier as drivers license but i’m still buzzing it’s here.
        4) the business falls again, even if it’s just one place down. i’ve always despised this trash so i hope it goes.
        5) i’m really rooting for summer 91 to be the next big edm smash! it climbed to number 64 this week, so i really hope it enters the top 40 soon.

        thanks for reading! :)
